title: Economic Crosscurrents Heading Into 2026
description: Jobs data sent mixed signals into the holidays as hiring cooled and unemployment edged higher. But consumers are still spending, inflation is easing, and rate cuts remain in play for 2026. Jennifer Lee, Senior Economist at BMO Capital Markets joins us on what’s flashing yellow and where the real landmines are ahead. (Source: Bloomberg)
